!! Using a regexp on a caption field

The following filter example will find all tiddlers with `VirtualBox` tags excluding any caption (Can use any field) that has the word `Mount`

<div id=bd>

Using `Advanced Search filter`, syntax is:

```
[tag[VirtualBox]]-[regexp:caption[Mount]]
```
[tag[VirtualBox]]-[regexp:caption[Mount]]

</div>
<br />
<div id=bd>

To use the filter in a tiddler need to surround the filter with 3 braces

```
{{{ [tag[VirtualBox]]-[regexp:caption[Mount]] }}}
```

{{{ [tag[VirtualBox]]-[regexp:caption[Mount]] }}}
</div>
<br />
<div id=bd>

```
<<list-links filter:[tag[VirtualBox]]-[regexp:caption[Mount]]>>
```
<<list-links filter:[tag[VirtualBox]]-[regexp:caption[Mount]]>>
</div>

If you replace the `-` with `+` then find `VirtualBox` tag and must have the regexp `Mount` in the caption field.

If you remove the `-` or `+` it becomes an `or`


<div id=bd>

!! The following example will display caption with tags on second line. 

```c-like
<table>
<$list filter="[tag[VirtualBox]]+[regexp:caption[Mount]]">
	<tr>
		<td><<currentTiddler>></td>
		<td>{{||$:/core/ui/ViewTemplate/tags}}</td>
	</tr>
</$list>
</table>
```
